<br>
I don't understand what she is trying to prove. It's a known fact that women can't drive the ball as far as a man, so she can't compete in that aspect. She already proved she can't make it to the green on a 500yd hole in the same amount of strokes as the male players of her caliber. <br>
<br>
Personally, I don't like her there just for the simple fact that she is making this end up as a media circus, and a basic publiciity stunt. <br>
<br>
You know why men don't go to the women's leagues? BECAUSE THEY AREN'T ALLOWED! The WNBA, LPGA, Women's Tennis, WPBL, WBC. All of them do not allow men to compete as they are women only leagues. However, when a men's league doesn't allow it, it's sexist. Welcome to the world of the double standard!<br>
<br>
I seem to remember a few years back there was a female goalie who played for an NHL team, I want to say the Tampa Bay Lightning(Correct me if I am wrong). She didn't last too long, why? Women's bodies are not designed to take the punishment that can be dealt by a grueling season such as the NHL or the NFL. So why is the PGA any different? <br>
<br>
Anyway, I hope she chokes, and realizes that this was all a big mistake. Don't get me wrong, she is an excellent golfer, and would blow me out of the water any day of the week (hey I got a 32 handicap ok =p). Although, the one thing that really did bug me, when they asked her what Tee Box she was gonna be hitting from she was quoted as saying &quot;I guess I will have to hit it from where they hit from&quot; . Well no shit Sherlock! (For those who don't know, women generally hit from a Tee Box that is anywhere from 10-50 feet and in some cases 100 feet further forward than the Pro Tee Box).<br>
<br>
