orts if they can qualify like the rest of the competitors. I dont think it's fair to a man to have to box or wrestle against a women for many reason. But in sports like Golf, Tennis, swimming, running, etc. i dont see why a woman shouldn’t be able to match her skills to other men if she is capable.<br>
<br>
In tennis to make it into the main draw for a major tournament you have to qualify. If a women is able to do this i dont see what the big deal is. If a women is given special treatment and is allowed special rules (see battle of the sexes) Then the whole thing is pretty much bullshit.<br>
<br>
Golf is even more of a sport where a good women player should be able to compete against men. Golf is &quot;one of those sports&quot; where you dont even compete against other players in the true sense You compete against yourself. Same with sports like running, swimming, weightlifting, etc. Basically your opponent's actions have no effect on your play as would be the case in a sport like tennis, wrestling, football, soccer etc.. So if a women can lift more weight than a man i dont see why that should not be recognized in that regard<br>
<br>
Im guarantee you %100 that Anika will not come close to winning, but if she is able to place 80th out of 100 players then her point is valid. She should have to qualify like all other players on the same terms. If she doesnt then tough luck.<br>
<br>
