<br>
She isn't taking any slots that a normal PGA player would take, because she got a sponsor's exemption.  Usually these go to Celebrities, CEOs, or Amateurs anyways.<br>
<br>
She picked the Colonial because it's the shortest course and because it's an invitational (smaller amount of participants).<br>
<br>
As far as qualifying, that remains to be seen.  There are plenty of players on the PGA that got their tour card without going to Q-school.  Tiger Woods, Phil Mickleson, Davis Love III, Fred Couples, Jack Nicklaus, Arnold Palmer to name a few, all got their starts with sponsor exemptions.<br>
<br>
As far as a woman playing on the &quot;mens&quot; tour, there actually isn't any such thing as the &quot;mens&quot; tour.  No where in the PGA bylaws does it state that you have to be a male to play on the tour (unlike the LPGA which states you must be female).<br>
<br>
As for the media circus, this wasn't generated by her.  She's said over and over that she simply wanted to see how she stands.  She's already the best in the LPGA, this is just a logical progression to see if she can cut it.<br>
<br>
