<br>
My problem here is not that a woman is going to compete with the men.<br>
<br>
No, My problem stems from the fact that she has not achieved a station in her own sport of dominance.  She is GOOD.  She is one of the best the women have to offer, but she hasn't &quot;Done it all&quot; in women's golf.  She hasn't won every tournament, or even a Vast majority.  She is not the Tiger Woods of women's golf. <br>
<br>
She hasn't completed a grand slam of major events, or even a &quot;Tiger Slam&quot; of majors.  She is not blowing the women she competes with away Every tournament she enters, and it isn't like she no longer has comperable competition in her sport. <br>
<br>
Why should she now ascend to this?<br>
